	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm listening to it right now! <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" />
<br />
<br />Right off the bat I notice you have the same problem I do: trying to read &amp; sound natural. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> 
<br />
<br />You could adlib, but if you're like me (not a good talker) then this is <em>probably</em> not a good option.
<br />
<br />Actors have this same problem (&amp; they're not even reading!). You just need to keep practicing; it will eventually come.
<br />
<br />As for the sound mixing, I think it's okay. Some people might think the music needs to brought up more, but it's really up to you. I think it works as it is right now - it's not distracting.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


