	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The Nerd did a "Behind the scenes" video about how he balances volume levels when he does his reviews.  He uses video editing software that makes it easy to separately do simple effects to multiple different audio/video sources.  He basically fades the game audio down while he's talking, and unfades it back up when he's done speaking.  Then when he stitches many clips of game footage together, he crossfades the game music so the cuts are less noticeable.
<br />He also mentioned that he forgot to do color correction when he did the "Silver Surfer" video, and is embarrassed about that.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


